I figured I would have to give up the backward d pawn.  But I was ok with that, we would be even in material, but I like my pawn structure and postion better. I had faced the dreaded Austrian Attack formation and chip away at it till it was no more. That all you can ask from a opening really, the rest is up to the player.  The Pirc gave me pariaty going into the middlegame, which means the Pirc defense did its job.  I like Qb6 I think Pirc players who run into the Austrian Attack should give it a look.
